<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-189-160 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 697 827</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Technology  April 1991 v7 n4 p95(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Mandamp;T Publishing 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Pivotal's 10-Base-T hubs. (Pivotal Technologies Inc. introducesMAUcard Plus internal hub) (New Products ) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Pivotal Technologies Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Pivotal Technologies MAUcard Plus (Network hub) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionNetwork Hubs10BaseT.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Pivotal Technologies Inc. has introduced the MAUcard Plus, a 10Base-Tinternal hub.andP;  Pivotal has also introduced the FlexiHub, a 10Base-T modularinternal hub that provides up to 12 ports.andP;  Both the MAUcard Plus and TheFlexiHub half-size add-in cards are fully compliant with the IEEE 802.3istandard.andP;  They offer full repeater signal regeneration and independent portauto-partitioning and reconnection.andP;  Both offer a BNC port for cascadingadditional units homogeneously (MAUcard to MAUcard and FlexiHub to FlexiHub).andM;The BNC port also provides thin coaxial Ethernet-to-10Base-T connectivity forboth products.andP;  The MAUcard can be inserted inside the file server andconnects four users via 10Base-T ports.andP;  The FlexiHub also installs in theserver and connects six, eight, 10, or 12 users via 10Base-T ports calledHubSimms.andP;  Each HubSimm provides two ports, and the base FlexiHub comes withthree HubSimms (six ports) installed.andM;The MAUcard Plus retails for $499.andP;  The base, six-port FlexiHub retails for$600, and additional HubSimms are $150 each.andP;  Contact Pivotal TechnologiesInc., 18240 Purdue Drive, Saratoga, CA 95070; 408-374-7887.andM;Circle reader service number 262</TEXT></DOC>